The quote from our waiter at 8:30pm: “We’re all out of pizza, and all out of tacos”... after we already sat here drinking and looking for 20 minutes.  This place is a joke.
Service was slow and food was sub-par.

Plenty of room and a great long bar. Tons of beers to choose from and the server was really nice. They have a game room with a pool table and various arcade games.  The pool table was not level and had some serious grooves in the felt, made the play at any skill level relatively impossible. I still enjoyed the game room for the big couches and the big buck hunter.  All the food I had was terrible and is why I rated so low. The Nachos were swimming in moisture from the meat causing them to be soggy (massive portion though). The pulled pork sliders tasted like they had been left in a crock pot forever. The Detroit style pizza (which I was super excited for since its hard to find in NYC) was also soggy, no crispy bottom and just flat on flavors. It seems the red peppers they used were from a jar with water and put under the cheese so they just drowned the crust in moisture. While I didn't try it the mac and cheese was described as OK, at $17 dollars with bacon I would hope so. The prices weren't bad but, since it was all mostly not edible it was not worth it.  They need to get a new cook/chef in here. If you're looking for a bar to just drink at, stop in for the friendly staff and big selection of drinks. Just don't order the food.​

It's A pretty Chill Place, I like the menu The Cocktail I had was The OLD BLUE EYES, 🤓Niiiiice OH yeah💪🏾, I like the place because it's not to many people hear, it's like you have your own privacy read books ETC.

Friendly service, good drinks selection, and plenty of space for parties of all types make this an easy destination for a hip but unpretentious drink or meal in downtown Brooklyn. Food is generally pretty good too, if a bit over-spiced on my last visit.

The ambiance is great! Big open space. Great sports bar feel. The game room is awesome. The food is sub-par at best.  I had the General Tso Chicken and waffles. The wings were fine but the waffles were super dry as if they frozen. Also, they don't use regular waffle batter. It smelled of yeast kinda like pizza dough. My friend had the Irish biscuits and grits, soda  bread bacon and sausage in parsley sauce which was tasty. But she got was 3 pieces of toasted Italian bread instead of. She tasted no bacon whatsoever. The coffee machine was busted so no Joe during brunch. The service was good considering that the poor bartender/server (Robin) was running around like a chicken with his head cutoff. The red headed hostess didn't even think to help him run drinks or food to the tables.  In conclusion, I won't be coming back here.

The menu here is fantastic - been here for brunch (shrimp and grits with a fried egg on top) and dinner (warm brussels sprouts salad). And they have a nice beer selection and full bar as well. I really can't understand why this place isn't packed every day, but I assume that once NHL season starts they will be bustling.

Food was good....when 3 out of 8 of us finally got it after waiting over an hour. Place was not crowded; really just lousy service, forgotten orders and understaffed. Isn't the hostess supposed to be friendly? So the other 5 people in our party never received thier food, and 4 of them never got their drink. We complained to the manager, and he did the right thing and we didn't get a bill......but we left hungry and thirsty!!  John Taffer....go rescue this place!!!

Vibe and environment is solid, and they have a decent beer selection for a trendy sports bar. But the service is pretty terrible, especially for the above-average prices.  Been here a few different times, and the result has always been similar: 1) Went before a concert at Barclay's Center, and the place, surprisingly, wasn't that crowded. Nevertheless, the place was understaffed on an event night and it took at least 10 minutes just to get a couple of beers despite the modest crowd and open spaces at the bar. 2) Went for drinks on a weeknight when there was no event accross the street. The place was pretty empty, but it still took forever to get served, and didn't receive the whole order when we did get served. Then got attitude from the bartender when we asked for the items they had forgotten. 3) Went on a crowded Saturday night. A decent crowd but still a good amount of open spots at the bar. Took way longer than it should have for a bartender to take notice. Then getting them to close the tab out later took forever as well, I almost just left my card there and ordered a new one.  The place should be really cool, but it's a super frustrating to go to currently.

Great place for a quick drink before events at Barclay's.

The food was good, the staff attentive at times. My friend and I went there on a Saturday afternoon. It was not that busy, but it took about 20 minutes to get a server's attention to take our order. We ordered the Creole Shrimp Toast, Beet Salad, Lemongrass Pork Salad, and the side of Buffalo Cauliflower with Blue Cheese. The food was phenomenal, the ambience was wonderful, the management was great in making sure that everything was good with our meal, but the waitstaff were most likely understaffed. After we finished our meal and had dessert, it took nearly 20 minutes just to get our check.  There are probably some kinks that need to be worked out with respect to the waitstaff. All other aspects of our meal were rather pleasant. This restaurant is still new and it's clear that they are actively making and effort to improve their efficiency. I cannot wait to try their food again in another month or two. I'm sure by then they will be even better!

Staff was friendly (after noticing I was there) but once the food wasn't up to par with expectations it's a lost case.  I can even deal with subpar service if the food was good.
